FBIS4-39983 "drsov113_b_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military, Nuclear & Space Issues Grachev Says 300,000 Troops To Be Cut by Oct Grachev Says 300,000 Troops To Be Cut by Oct LD1306095694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 13 Jun 94 LD1306095694 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Russian BFN [Text] The authorized strength of the Russian Armed Forces would be 1.9 million by 1 October 1994, Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev told Interfax. At present, the authorized strength of the Russian Armed Forces is 2.2 million. Grachev noted that it was not only the rank-and-file and officer corps which were to be cut -- general officers were to be cut, too. He said that 270 generals' posts would be cut by the end of the year.
